// Data Types in JS 
// 1. String ==> Text ('hello', 'world')
// 2. Number ==> numbers(10, 324)
// 3. Boolean ==> true / false
// 4. Null ==> khali (intentionly empty)
// 5. Undefiend ==> jb value assign na ki gyi ho 
// 6. Object ==> complex data (array, objects)

